During my internship at Unified Mentor, I worked on standalone projects that helped me gain practical experience in full-stack development.

1. Document Management System:
I built a platform where users can store, access, and manage their documents easily. The system allows document sharing with edit permissions, making collaboration smooth and secure. It’s a fully authenticated, modular, and optimized application. I used Appwrite as the backend service to handle authentication and storage, and focused on improving the frontend performance for a better user experience.

2. Online Code Editor:
In this project, I developed both the frontend and backend, gaining a strong grip on full-stack development. I used Express.js, JWT for authentication, and MongoDB for database management. The editor allows users to write and run code through external APIs and view the output instantly. It also supports real-time collaboration using Socket.io, where multiple users can see live updates while one person is editing at a time.

I also explored deployment platforms like Vercel and Render to host and manage these applications.
For my performance and contributions, I was ranked among the top 10 interns during the internship.

